  <modalFeedback identifier="CORRECT_FEEDBACK" outcomeIdentifier="GENERAL_FEEDBACK" showHide="show">
    <p>
      <b>Option D (Diabetes insipidus) is Correct.</b>
      Cranial diabetes insipidus is caused by head injury, infection (meningitis or abscess), cerebrovascular accident or malignancy. There is a high plasma osmolality and low urine osmolality due to impaired vasopressin secretion from the posterior pituitary. A water deprivation test is used to investigate disease presence.
    </p>
  </modalFeedback>
